node.text: my biggest piece of workout advice? build a routine that works for you! so today, in partnership with @gymshark, i’m sharing a go-to cardio workout that i know will always make me sweat. be sure to modify it for your skill level, stay hydrated, & let me know in the comments how it goes!! (thanks @gymshark for partnering with me #ad)

node.text: Before there were the festivals, parades and concerts, there was the Christopher Street Liberation Day March - the first pride march, one year after Stonewall. (learn more: @LGBT_History, animation: @victoriambarranco)

node.title: The Path To Pride (From Stonewall to the First Pride March)

node.text:
GET FIT: Ep 26: Season 1 Bloopers - as a special lil treat to close out season 1 of #GETFITwithTyler, please enjoy this shitshow blooper reel. listen, we filmed ALL of the episodes in two days, so of course my brain was... a LITTLE fried. 

thank you everyone who gave so much love to this lil series!! if you enjoyed it, let me know what kind of episodes you’d like to see if i make a season 2… ;) thank you @j_gonzy1 for all the tips & tricks to a great workout, & to the crew & team who helped create such a fun project - can’t believe we pulled it off!

note: this series was created prior to social distancing & when self quarantines were suggested. make sure to use #GETFITwithTyler to share your workout progress on your story so i can see & repost!!

node.text: #ad hearing a song & immediately sending it to someone you know will love it?? that’s my friendship with @koreykuhl - we’ve known each other for almost 15 years, & our love for music is one way we keep in touch, even now cities apart. when we’re not frolicking together at a music festival, we’re sending songs & playlists we think the other will appreciate. sometimes, a simple playlist can help a friend, a colleague, a family member, or an acquaintance get to know you better. this pride, I’m excited to partner with @indeedworks to celebrate a special concert with @mikainstagram, showing how music can tell our stories & the simple act of sharing a playlist can create a more empathetic workplace or community. wanna listen?? link in my insta story!
